name: R1orientation:  left means that read1 is to the left of the rearrangement junction and read2 is to the right
All inversion translocations are compatible due to possibility of a balanced translocation
All non-inverted translocations (rows 10-13) are compatible due to possibility of a balanced translocation

Only columns B, C, D, and F can be used to classify probable rearrangement types.  Column E (read orientation) can only be determined if the data is consistent with normal, deletion, amp1 & amp3, etc.
